         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0889">
               <p>A wealthy landholder of <placeName>Garth, Wales</placeName>, and loyal member of
                  the Established Church, Gwynne was drawn into the evangelical revival in <date
                     when="1737">1737</date> through the preaching of <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers0950.xml"/>Howell Harris</persName>, and began offering
                  support to the leaders of the revival, including the Wesley brothers.
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2176.xml"/>CW</persName> met
                  Gwynne&apos;s daughter <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2191.xml"
                     />Sarah</persName> in <date when="1747-08">August 1747</date> and they were
                  married in <date when="1749-04">April 1749</date>. Thus letters between Marmaduke
                  and the Wesley brothers concern not only plans for evangelistic visits but
                  negotiations over the pending wedding and continuing family matters. See <hi
                     rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 497; and Vickers, <hi rend="italic">Dictionary</hi>,
                  145.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
